# Documentation updates

When a change alters user-visible behavior, hardware, storage, or APIs, update the matching docs in the **same PR** as the code. Do not leave documentation for a follow-up unless the issue explicitly scopes docs-only work.

## What requires a doc pass

Update docs if the change touches any of:

- Pin maps, pump count, optional hardware, or wiring
- Calibration, profiles, NVS/LittleFS storage, or Factory Reset
- Web UI flows or HTTP API fields/endpoints
- Flash/upload survival (`upload`, `uploadfs`, OTA)
- Features listed in README or phased status in DESIGN.md
- BOM quantities or part assumptions

## Where to update

| Change type | Primary docs |
|-------------|--------------|
| Pins / wiring / multi-pump hardware | `README.md` pin tables, `docs/WIRING.md`, `docs/HARDWARE.md` |
| Features / product capabilities | `README.md` Features, `docs/DESIGN.md` |
| Storage / flash survival | `README.md` Notes, `docs/DESIGN.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md` |
| Parts / quantities | `docs/BOM.md` |
| Doc index / links | `docs/README.md` |

Also update `docs/README.md` descriptions when a doc’s role changes.

## Checklist before opening the PR

- [ ] README does not contradict the new behavior (especially pins and features).
- [ ] HARDWARE.md / WIRING.md match `Config.h` / `platformio.ini` defaults.
- [ ] DESIGN.md phase/status and storage notes still accurate.
- [ ] No stale “single pump only” or wiped-by-uploadfs claims for NVS-backed data.

## Examples

- Adding `pump_4` pins → README + HARDWARE + WIRING (+ BOM if parts scale).
- Moving settings keys → DESIGN storage section + README Notes if survival changes.
- New Diagnostics control → README Features and the relevant HARDWARE section.
